<font color="#FF0000">SOME EXPERIENCES,  A QUESTION</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jul 31  9:11:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Five years ago, when the repressed images and feelings of my Vietnam experience began to silently explode across my inner landscape, at the beginning of my journey, when I did not know it was a journey I had begun, the Eagle came to me in that place of walking without walking, and said to me &quot;follow, learn, and observe&quot;. I began to seek images of the Eagle. Belt buckles, the painting from my grandfather's bedroom, a golden Eagle carved into snowflake obsidian, and, now, even computer images, capture my imagination. Each image has its own special power. It was the Eagle who guided me to the Wall. <br><br>
...&quot;It  was early in the morning, the night scent still rising from the earth, the grass, and the yellow cast of the new day had still not fled. I stood at a threshold, a gateway, a path, to a time, a place, of the past, my past. I knew this would lead me to my longing, a pathway to my soul. Do I have the courage, I asked myself? Is this a rite of passage? I think it is.&quot;...<br><br>
...&quot;It is an entity, a being, a mystical folded form, dihedral, a wing, a phoenix struggling to rise from the earth, slicing its green bonds to escape, to freedom, to the sky, to release. Its feathers are the names of men who died, and the souls of those who lived. The souls are invisible. I know mine is there, somewhere.&quot;...<br><br>
The Wall is the Eagle bound to the earth. I am both the Eagle who is bound and the Eagle who is free. <br><br>
Many months ago when I was traveling, a ring in a shop caught my eye. It was very unusual, and unconventional. I was drawn to it, and I purchased it. Several months later when in a shop purchasing sage, other smudge items, and another Eagle image, the proprietor, a Native American, asked if she could hold my ring. After a long contemplative silence, she returned the ring saying that it was a medicine ring and that it had a lot of power.<br><br>
The ring has an Inner Circle at its center, the immovable place where the East, South, West, and North, all have balanced power...<br><br>
...and now I find myself there.<br><br>
I am both frightened and at peace with this. It *is*, however, and I am bound to it.<br><br>
--------------------<br><br>
I have a question. <br><br>
One of my most troubling shackles is the sound of a *human being* being tortured and I completely powerless.<br><br>
Does anyone have any thoughts on something like this? <br><br>
    
